definition (en): Camera master or COM recorder master.
scope note (en): Used for all master films that are made on archival stock in accordance with archival productions standards and that are given archival storage under relevant ISO standards.

definition (en): Any generation employed mainly for the production of other microforms.
scope note (en): Used for all masters that are not manufactured, produced, and stored in accordance with archival standards.

definition (en): Microform made from another microform that is intended primarily for use rather than for production of other microforms.
A combination of generations of film.
